body:
----- Original Message ----
From: On Ali 

> Is there a perl equivalent to PHP variables $_POST and $_GET?

It would be easy to create, but what you really want is the CGI module:

  #!/usr/bin/perl

  use strict;
  use warnings;

  use CGI ':standard';
  my $id    = param('id');
  my $name  = param('name');
  my @sports = param('sport');  # e.g. sport=basketball;sport=football

Cheers,
Ovid

